title.narrative: Communication and advocacy programmes are aligned to global and regional priorities

description.narrative: ESARO continued to deliver against the global advocacy strategy and adapt to unforeseen situations at the regional level, including universal birth registration, ending harmful practices, WASH, education, and nutrition. Robust support was provided to COs on youth advocacy and engagement, on the impacts of climate change, as well as school reopening during COVID-19. Consistently, throughout the year, in line to global and regional priorities, ESARO engaged with media partners to ensure coverage of child-related issues in top-tier media while also using digital platforms to raise awareness and advocate for positive solutions to further the lives of children and their families.; | Status:Met | As-of Date:21/03/2022
